<HEAD>Police Discover Drug `Refinery' in Villa; Arrest Five</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOLOGNA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police on Tuesday said they discovered a
cocaine refinery in a villa, leading to the arrest of two Italians
and three Colombians and the seizure of 4.4 pounds of pure cocaine.
   The coca paste used to produce the cocaine was smuggled into
Italy mixed with cardboard, which was then used to line suitcase
bottoms, the officers told the Italian news agency ANSA reported.
   Four of those arrested have been accused of criminal association
aimed at drug production and importation as well as drug possession,
ANSA said. A fifth has been accused of selling and possessing drugs,
ANSA said.
   The investigation began after 2.2 pounds of cocaine were seized
in Bologna in January, leading to the arrest of seven people,
including four Peruvians, police said.
