<HEAD>Nicaragua Accuses Honduras of Border Attacks</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Nicaragua</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANAGUA, Nicaragua (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The government claimed Wednesday that
Honduran soldiers fired on Nicaraguan border posts 13 times this
year.
   A Defense Ministry statement said the latest incident was a
mortar attack Sunday on the Murupuchi outpost in Nuevo Segovia
province, 110 miles north of Managua. It did not mention casualties.
   On Monday, the ministry accused Honduran troops of firing three
