<FIRST>r w AM-Steroids     02-28 0153</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Steroids,150</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bill Would Ban Mailing Steroids</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two senators introduced legislation Tuesday
that would ban the use of the mails to distribute athletic
performance-enhancing steroids.
   ``The use of these potentially life-threatening drugs is one of
the most serious problems facing our nation today,'' Sen. Strom
Thurmond, R-S.C., said in a statement issued by his office.
   The bill, co-sponsored by Sen. Joseph R. Biden Jr., D-Del., would
make it a crime, punishable by three years in prison, to use the
mails to distribute anabolic steroids, drugs used by some athletes
to enhance performance.
   Use of the mails to solicit sales of steroids also would become a
criminal offense under the legislation.
   Congress last year banned steroid distribution, but authorities
say some dealers, particularly in Mexico and Europe, are using the
mails and telephone solicitation to get steroids to users.
   The latest legislation would enable postal inspectors to join the
battle.
</TEXT>
