<FIRST>r p AM-ChicagoMayors-List     02-28 0172</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Chicago Mayors-List,0177</SECOND>
<HEAD>Daley Would Become City's 6th Mayor in 13 Years</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Richard M. Daley, who won Tuesday's Democratic
mayoral primary, would become the city's sixth mayor in the last 13
years if he wins the general election April 4. Here is a list of the
others:
   _ Richard J. Daley, elected in 1955, served for 21 years until
his death in December 1976.
   _ Michael Bilandic, acting mayor following Daley's death in 1976;
elected by voters in 1977 to fill the final two years of Daley's
four-year term; defeated in the 1979 Democratic primary by Jane
Byrne.
   _ Jane Byrne, elected in 1979, lost in the 1983 Democratic
primary in a three-way race with Richard M. Daley and Harold
Washington.
   _ Harold Washington, elected in 1983 as the city's first black
mayor; re-elected in 1987; died on Nov. 25, 1987, seven months into
his second term.
   _ Eugene Sawyer, named acting mayor by City Council on Dec. 2,
1987; defeated in the Democratic primary Feb. 28, 1989.
