<TEXT>
   The stock market was higher in early trading
today.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was up 6.25 points at
2,256.61 at 11 a.m. EST.
   Advancing issues edged out declines by around 6 to 5 on the New
York Stock Exchange, with 630 issues up, 460 down and 575 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board totaled 44.58 million shares.
   Analysts said the market's advance was being generated mainly by
its own steam. They cautioned against attaching undue significance
to a government report today on economic growth, since it refers to
