<FIRST>u f BC-Britain-Stocks 1stLd-Writethru   02-28 0180</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru,0187</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Shares Close Higher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices on the London Stock Exchange rallied
to close higher Tuesday but trading was thin ahead of Wednesday's
release of the nation's January trade report.
   At the close, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index
was up 5.7 points, or 0.3 percent, at 2,002.4, its best level for
the day.
   The late-day rally was prompted mostly by good gains on Wall
Street, where the Dow Jones industrial average was up about 12
points as London trading ended.
   Volume was light, however, with 357.8 million shares traded,
compared with Monday's 413.8 million shares.
   Recent concerns that British interest rates may have to move
higher were set aside momentarily as the pound showed renewed
strength against the West German mark, dealers said.
   But they cautioned that a disappointing set of figures on
Britain's balance of payments could undermine the pound and possibly
prompt an interest rate rise.
   ``The underlying level of interest is still fairly low. We're all
really waiting for the next set of trade figures,'' a dealer said.
</TEXT>
