<FIRST>r f BC-USWest-Cable     02-28 0423</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-US West-Cable,0435</SECOND>
<HEAD>US West Bids On Hong Kong Cable Television System</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ENGLEWOOD, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   US West International said Tuesday it had
formed a consortium that submitted a bid for what it said would be
the world's biggest cable television franchise in Hong Kong.
   The franchise winner would be entitled to build a cable system
that would serve between 1.5 million and 2 million homes, more homes
than in any other single cable franchise territory, US West said.
   US West International, which is a unit of the former Bell System
company US West, already has interests in cable television systems
in France and Great Britain.
   Reynie Ortiz, president of US West International, said in a news
release issued by the company that the successful bidder will be
granted two 15-year licenses, one for cable TV programming and the
other for non-voice telecommunications services using cable
facilities. He said the latter system could include fax, videotex
and private networks within buildings or within certain geographic
areas of Hong Kong.
   The Hong Kong government is expected to announce the successful
bidder in August, said Ortiz.
   ``Hong Kong is an extremely attractive market for us, since it
affords the opportunity to combine telecommunications and cable
technology,'' said Ortiz. ``It fits perfectly with our strategy of
being a worldwide player in the cable-telecommunications arena. And,
significantly, it positions us for eventual penetration into the
vast Asian and Chinese mainland markets.''
   US West International spokesman Ed Mattix said his company has a
25 percent stake in the consortium which is called Hong Kong Cable
Communications Ltd.
   He said other members of the consortium are Wharf Holdings, a
major Hong Kong commercial and residential development firm with a
28 percent stake; Sun Hung Kai, a large Hong Kong-based construction
and development company with 27 percent; Coditel, one of Europe's
largest cable TV companies with a 10 percent interest, and Shaw
Brothers, a major Asian film and television production company also
with 10 percent interest.
   US West International previously acquired a 10 percent interest
in Lyonnaise Communications, which operates cable TV franchises in
France. Coditel is a partner in that venture as well.
   US West International also has interests in two
cable-telecommunications ventures in the United Kingdom. One of
those franchises, in Birmingham, England, has 500,000 households on
line.
   Another US West unit, US West Communications, provides telephone
service to 14 Western states. US West also owns companies involved
in commercial real estate, financial services, cellular mobile
communications and paging, directory publishing and business
telecommunications products and services.
</TEXT>
