<HEAD>Energy Prices Mixed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The recent rally in the heating oil pits ran out
of energy Tuesday, with futures prices pulling back slightly.
   However, gasoline futures rose and crude oil prices posted slim
gains.
   On the New York Mercantile Exchange, wholesale home heating oil
for March delivery fell 0.20 cent to settle at 52.45 cents a gallon.
The April contract was off 0.19 cent at 50.19 cents.
   John H. O'Connell, an analyst at Refco Inc., said heating oil
prices have gone up recently due to tight supplies and buying ahead
of the expiration Tuesday of the March contract.
   March unleaded gasoline rose 0.14 cent to end the day at 50.81
cents a gallon. The April contract gained 0.09 cent, settling at
51.57 cents.
   Crude oil prices were steady to modestly higher. The April
contract for the benchmark U.S. crude, West Texas Intermediate,
gained 1 cent to finish at $18.15 a barrel.
