<FIRST>r f AM-FordRecall     02-28 0127</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Ford Recall,0133</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ford Recalls 246,000 1983 Model Cars</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DEARBORN, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ford Motor Co. on Tuesday recalled about
246,000 1983 model cars because of potential problems with emission
control systems.
   The company said vehicles included in the recall are Ford
Mustang, Capri and Thunderbird models along with Mercury Cougar, LTD
and Marquis cars.
   The recall affects all of the cars equipped with 3.8-liter, V-6
engines, except those built for sale in California, where state law
requires special pollution control systems.
   Ford said the federal Environmental Protection Agency had
determined that some of the cars emitted excessive levels of carbon
monoxide and hydrocarbons.
   Owners of the cars will be notified by mail and repairs will be
performed at no cost to the customer, Ford said.
</TEXT>
